Extrahepatic portal venous obstruction can be associated with bile duct 
abnormalities, the entity being called portal biliopathy. Three cases are 
reported of extrahepatic bile duct strictures in patients with portal biliopathy 
who developed haemobilia during endotherapy. Although endoscopic therapy with 
